  "Question": "<p>I'm trying to show the following:</p> <blockquote> <blockquote> <p>If <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_426\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x,y\\geq 0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, then <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_427\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"(x+y)^{k}\\geq x^{k}+y^{k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <msup> <mi>y</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> for all <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_428\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k\\in\\mathbb{R_{\\geq 1}}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msub> <mi>R</mi> <mrow> <mi></mi> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </msub> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span></p> </blockquote> </blockquote> <p>So, far I've tried a few things, but nothing seems to stick. Clearly <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_429\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x\\leq x+y\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> and since both sides of the inequality are positive, the inequality <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_430\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{k}\\leq(x+y)^{k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2264</mo> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </math></span> will hold for <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_431\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k\\geq 1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. Similarly, <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_432\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"y^{k}\\leq(x+y)^{k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mi>y</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2264</mo> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>. Adding both inequalities together, we obtain: <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_433\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x^{k}+y^{k}\\leq 2(x+y)^{k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <msup> <mi>y</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> <mo>\u2264</mo> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>. While this is close, of course, it is not what we want to show.</p> <p>Alternatively, I was thinking that if we fix <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_434\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x,y\\geq 0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_435\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f(k)=(x+y)^{k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>k</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </math></span>, and let <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_436\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"g(k)=x^{k}+y^{k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>k</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <msup> <mi>y</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>, we can show using the binomial theorem that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_437\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"(x+y)^{r}\\geq x^{r}+y^{r}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>r</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>r</mi> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <msup> <mi>y</mi> <mi>r</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> for all <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_438\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"r\\in\\mathbb{Z^{+}}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>r</mi> <mo>\u2208</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <msup> <mi>Z</mi> <mo>+</mo> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span>. Then, if we can show both <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_439\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_440\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"g\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>g</mi> </math></span> intersect only when <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_441\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k=1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, we might have better luck proving the statement since then we would have <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_442\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?><math alttext=\"(x+y)^{r}&amp;gt;x^{r}+y^{r}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mi>r</mi></msup><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>r</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mi>r</mi></msup></mrow></mrow></math></span> for all positive integers <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_443\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"r\\geq 2\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>r</mi> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math></span>. A real number <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_444\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"m\\notin\\mathbb{Z}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>m</mi> <mo>\u2209</mo> <mrow> <merror class=\"ltx_ERROR undefined undefined\"> <mtext>\\mathbb</mtext> </merror> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mi>Z</mi> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> with the property that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_445\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f(m)=g(m)\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>f</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> <mo>=</mo> <mrow> <mi>g</mi> <mo>\u2062</mo> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mi>m</mi> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> could not then exist since then that would violate the fact that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_446\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k=1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span> is the only intersection. We could then invoke the continuity of <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_447\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_448\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"g\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>g</mi> </math></span> together with the fact that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_449\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?><math alttext=\"(x+y)^{r}&amp;gt;x^{r}+y^{r}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>y</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><mi>r</mi></msup><mo>&gt;</mo></mrow><mrow><msup><mi>x</mi><mi>r</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mi>y</mi><mi>r</mi></msup></mrow></mrow></math></span> for all positive integers <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_450\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"r\\geq 2\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>r</mi> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>2</mn> </mrow> </math></span> to obtain our result. Of course, all of this is dependent on rigorously showing that <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_451\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"f\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>f</mi> </math></span> and <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_452\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"g\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mi>g</mi> </math></span> intersect only when <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_453\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k=1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>.</p> <p>Otherwise, I'm running low on ideas. Any hints would be greatly appreciated.</p>",
  "Title": "Hints for showing that if <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_423\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"x,y\\geq 0\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>,</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>0</mn> </mrow> </math></span>, then <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_424\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"(x+y)^{k}\\geq x^{k}+y^{k}\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <msup> <mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo> <mrow> <mi>x</mi> <mo>+</mo> <mi>y</mi> </mrow> <mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo> </mrow> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mrow> <msup> <mi>x</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> <mo>+</mo> <msup> <mi>y</mi> <mi>k</mi> </msup> </mrow> </mrow> </math></span> for all <span class=\"math-container\" id=\"q_425\"><?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?> <math alttext=\"k\\geq 1\" display=\"block\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"> <mrow> <mi>k</mi> <mo>\u2265</mo> <mn>1</mn> </mrow> </math></span>",
